@startuml
skinparam maxMessageSize 150
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20
skinparam BoxPadding 10
autonumber

actor "User" as User
box "MCP Host (Spring Boot Application)" #LightCyan
participant "Spring AI\n(Host/Orchestrator)" as Host
participant "Gemini\n(LLM Engine)" as LLM
participant "MCP Client\n(Universal Translator)" as Client
end box

box "External Systems" #LightYellow
participant "MCP Server\n(Java Microservice)" as Server
database "PostgreSQL\n(Ledger/Txn DB)" as DB
end box

== 1. Initialization & Tool Discovery ==
Host -> Client: Initialize ARDA Agent
note right: The Spring Boot app starts up and prepares the agent's context.
Client -> Server: JSON-RPC: listTools()
Server --> Client: Returns standard JSON menu\n(getTransactionStatus, getLedgerStatus)
Client --> Host: Registers available tools into context

== 2. The User Request ==
User -> Host: "My transaction UPI-12345 failed, what is the policy?"
Host -> LLM: Send User Prompt + System Guardrails + Tool Schemas
note right: Gemini evaluates the prompt and realizes it needs external data.

== 3. First ReAct Loop: Fetching Transaction Status ==
LLM -> Host: Proprietary Tool Call Request:\ngetTransactionStatus("UPI-12345")
Host -> Client: Forward tool call
note right: The MCP Client translates Gemini's specific JSON format into the universal MCP standard.
Client -> Server: JSON-RPC: executeCommand("getTransactionStatus", {"id": "UPI-12345"})
Server -> DB: Execute Java @Tool method
DB --> Server: Transaction Record
Server --> Client: Standardized Response:\n{"status": "FAILED", "reason": "BANK_SERVER_TIMEOUT"}
Client --> Host: Translate back to LLM format
Host -> LLM: Inject Tool Observation back into Context Window

== 4. Second ReAct Loop: Fetching Ledger Status ==
LLM -> Host: Proprietary Tool Call Request:\ngetLedgerStatus("UPI-12345")
note right: The AI autonomously realizes it lacks ledger data to calculate the refund, so it pauses to call Tool #2.
Host -> Client: Forward tool call
Client -> Server: JSON-RPC: executeCommand("getLedgerStatus", {"id": "UPI-12345"})
Server -> DB: Execute Java @Tool method
DB --> Server: Ledger Record
Server --> Client: Standardized Response:\n{"accountDebited": true, "beneficiaryCredited": false}
Client --> Host: Translate back to LLM format
Host -> LLM: Inject Tool Observation back into Context Window

== 5. Synthesis & Final Generation ==
LLM -> Host: Generate Final Resolution\n(Stop Condition Reached)
note right: The LLM synthesizes the tool observations (FAILED timeout + Account Debited) with its RAG policy knowledge.
Host --> User: "Your transaction failed due to a timeout. Because your account was debited, you will receive a refund in T+1 days."

@enduml